


PHILADELPHIA, Sept. 20  /PRNewswire/ -- A bipartisan group of Pennsylvania's federal representatives are calling for increased funding of the SBDC program in the next federal budget (fiscal year 2005).  The increased funds would be used to expand the program to help more entrepreneurs start and grow successful businesses.  Leading the push for boosting the SBDC program are Senator Arlen Specter (R) and Representatives Joseph Hoeffel (D-13), Tim Holden (D-17), Joseph Pitts (R-16), Todd Platts (R-19), and Curt Weldon (R-7).